  "risk_regime": {
    "stance": "risk_on",
    "conviction": 70,
    "rationale": "8 of 10 members are explicitly risk_on (convictions 65\u201385, mean ~75); the other two (Thaler, Roughgarden) are research-only no_view and express no market posture \u2014 so there is no risk_off dissent to offset. The house posture is structurally bullish builder-optimism on infrastructure and long-horizon value creation, explicitly NOT on speculation: nearly every risk_on member pairs it with an anti-casino/anti-leverage/anti-memecoin filter and conditions optimism on regulatory survival. Consensus conviction is set at 70 \u2014 slightly below the risk_on members' mean \u2014 to reflect that two voices abstain and that the optimism is quality-filtered and regulation-contingent rather than a broad price/macro call.",
    "provenance": "grounded"
  },
  "notes": "Consensus formed by weighting each item on BOTH conviction and coverage; lone low-conviction views were faded and split views demoted. Highest-confidence house calls (high coverage + tight, recent conviction): restaking, l2-scaling, the ZK/SNARK proving family, ai-crypto (broadest coverage), and ETH as the consensus base-layer token. Loudest shared concern: speculation/casino culture, followed by US regulatory hostility and Big Tech platform power. THREE items are genuinely split and were deliberately neutralized or demoted: decentralization (cov 3 but members divided on real vs. theater), MEV (researchers vs. skeptics, no coherent direction), and BTC (technical critiques cut both ways \u2014 not a house short). Important caveat: this desk skews toward researchers, infra investors, and policy/legal voices, so the corpus is dominated by technology and structural theses rather than tradeable price calls \u2014 token-level views are sparse and ETH/L2/EIGEN reads are ecosystem enthusiasm, not price targets. Two members (Thaler, Roughgarden) contribute only cryptography/mechanism-design research and hold no market view. No items were invented beyond what members stated; member item names reused where possible. Related single-member items were rolled into their nearest multi-member theme (e.g., memecoins\u2192speculation-mispricing, zkvm/SNARK-subfields\u2192zk, regulation-by-enforcement/uncertainty\u2192crypto-policy-regulation, high-fdv-low-float/vc-token-rent-extraction\u2192deal-structuring)."
}